      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical Note</head>
         <p>Bamberger is a photographer and teacher; he teaches at the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill and resides in Mebane, N.C.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Collection Overview</head>
         <p>Collection consists of original black and white prints (thirty-nine 11x14's and one 8x10) and original color prints (thirty-one 11x14's) taken by Bamberger documenting the closing of the White Furniture Company of Mebane, N.C.  These are the original prints used in the production of the book<title xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">  Closing: The Life and Death of an American Factory</title> (1998) by Bamberger and Cathy N. Davidson.  There are also proofs, primarily 3x5 machine proofs and 8x10 proofs of images selected as firsts, alternates, and seconds for the book; and related materials.  Also included is a dummy of the book.</p>
      </scopecontent>
